WEBVTT

00:03.294 --> 00:04.255
Previously
on "Grey's Anatomy"...

00:04.255 --> 00:05.216
Kyle Diaz,
diagnosed with relapsing

00:05.216 --> 00:05.926
and remitting
multiple sclerosis.

00:05.926 --> 00:07.338
You and I are a lot alike.

00:07.338 --> 00:09.470
I told him maybe we would go out
when he got back from touring,

00:09.470 --> 00:10.551
and so we've been texting.

00:10.551 --> 00:12.303
[ Chuckling ] Oh --
"Guitar Hero"?

00:12.303 --> 00:14.895
If Jackson can make a case
that April committed fraud,

00:14.895 --> 00:17.058
he's get a shot at getting
full custody of that baby.

00:17.058 --> 00:18.349
I think
Jackson's gonna sue me.

00:18.349 --> 00:19.770
I tried
to take the high road.

00:19.770 --> 00:21.562
Apparently, the high road is
paved with restraining orders.

00:21.562 --> 00:23.484
The restraining order
was a mistake.

00:23.484 --> 00:24.905
You were my best friend, April.

00:24.905 --> 00:27.648
And we should treat each other
the way we did on this paper.

00:27.648 --> 00:28.699
Bailey gave me
the Preminger Grant.

00:28.699 --> 00:30.111
I'm gonna be miserable
without you.

00:30.111 --> 00:32.283
You can figure it out.
You will. You -- You should.

00:32.283 --> 00:33.454
I can totally go with her.

00:33.454 --> 00:34.955
You'll be able to see Sofia
whenever you want.

00:34.955 --> 00:37.538
My ex-wife wants to
move across the country
and take our daughter.

00:37.538 --> 00:40.291
It's a six-month suspension
from the Residency Program.

00:40.291 --> 00:42.163
I tried to save her.
They know that, right?

00:42.163 --> 00:44.215
I wanted to fire you.
I was talked down.

00:44.215 --> 00:46.627
Well,
I am sorry I disappoint you.

00:46.627 --> 00:48.669
That's all, Dr. Warren.

00:51.382 --> 00:52.973
♪ Catch me out
in somethin' 'bout ♪

00:52.973 --> 00:54.555
♪ Like quarter after 2:00,
2:00 ♪

00:54.555 --> 00:57.678
♪ I be pushin' buttons,
I be comin' down so cool ♪

00:57.678 --> 00:59.440
Meredith:
Surgeons are often evaluated

00:59.440 --> 01:00.851
on speed and efficiency.

01:00.851 --> 01:02.313
Did you brush
all of them?
Yes.

01:02.313 --> 01:03.684
Let me see.

01:03.684 --> 01:05.486
But that doesn't mean faster
is always better.

01:05.486 --> 01:07.358
Good girl.
Keep brushing.

01:07.358 --> 01:08.819
Maggie, where's --

01:08.819 --> 01:10.111
We're here.
Found them.

01:10.111 --> 01:11.992
Where?

01:11.992 --> 01:14.155
They were
under my pillow.

01:14.155 --> 01:16.247
Someone crawled into bed
with me last night.

01:16.247 --> 01:18.329
Who's crawling into whose bed?
Is DeLuca here?

01:18.329 --> 01:19.660
Ha! Definitely not.

01:19.660 --> 01:21.582
It's the wrong foot.
Aw!

01:21.582 --> 01:22.753
You jump the gun,

01:22.753 --> 01:24.585
you risk making
a wrong diagnosis.

01:24.585 --> 01:26.417
You know we're becoming
like cat ladies,

01:26.417 --> 01:27.918
and the children
are our cats.

01:27.918 --> 01:29.510
I'm not a cat lady just because
I stopped having se--

01:29.510 --> 01:30.761
Read the room.

01:30.761 --> 01:33.304
Yeah.
S-E-X with DeLuca.

01:33.304 --> 01:35.676
We don't always have the time
to think before we act.

01:35.676 --> 01:37.017
-Hey, Mommy.
-Yes?

01:37.017 --> 01:41.312
Why did Aunt Maggie stop
having S-E-X with DeLuca?

01:41.312 --> 01:44.104
♪ Choppin' on them thangs
like pimp ♪

01:44.104 --> 01:47.488
Because he couldn't handle
that she was his B-O-S-S.

01:47.488 --> 01:50.611
Do not ever date a man
who can't handle your P-O-W-E-R.

01:50.611 --> 01:51.942
Okay.

01:51.942 --> 01:53.944
They just
pick up everything.

01:53.944 --> 01:55.326
Got 'em all.
Good job.

01:55.326 --> 01:57.538
And that's
what gets us in trouble.

01:57.538 --> 01:58.829
Ben: I can't stand it.

01:58.829 --> 02:00.621
I mean, the other day, I was
sitting in a coffee place,

02:00.621 --> 02:02.293
and I thought, "Yeah,
I can be a barista."

02:02.293 --> 02:04.835
Why not? I was an
anesthesiologist for years.

02:04.835 --> 02:06.747
Now I just wake people up
for a living.

02:06.747 --> 02:08.749
Less-than-lateral move,
don't you think?

02:08.749 --> 02:11.172
Well, I got to do something.
I'm going stir crazy.

02:11.172 --> 02:12.423
I'm falling so far behind,

02:12.423 --> 02:14.345
I'm losing
so much O.R. time...

02:14.345 --> 02:16.016
You have more experience
than any of the other residents.

02:16.016 --> 02:17.348
Don't panic.
You're already ahead.

02:17.348 --> 02:18.679
It's funny, actually.

02:18.679 --> 02:21.392
You've been a doctor
longer than any of them.

02:21.392 --> 02:23.184
Been a doctor
longer than me.

02:23.184 --> 02:24.855
How is that funny?

02:24.855 --> 02:26.357
It's not.

02:26.357 --> 02:27.688
Yeah, it's really not.

02:27.688 --> 02:29.730
God, that coffee sounds really
good right now, doesn't it?

02:30.571 --> 02:32.152
Yeah.

02:32.152 --> 02:34.154
[ Dog barks in distance ]

02:34.154 --> 02:35.075
[ Bells jingle ]

02:35.075 --> 02:36.197
Man: Oh, hey.
Woman: Hey, yes.

02:36.197 --> 02:37.238
Did you see
what happened in the paper?

02:37.238 --> 02:38.279
No. But you were right
about it.

02:38.279 --> 02:39.950
Hi. Sorry.
I'm here, I'm here.

02:39.950 --> 02:41.121
Arizona: Oh, no, no, no,
no, no. No.

02:41.121 --> 02:42.373
Hey. Um,
did you want to order?

02:42.373 --> 02:43.874
No, I'm good.
And you have a consult, right?

02:43.874 --> 02:45.666
Yeah, I do. Yeah.
Yeah, so we should
probably just...

02:45.666 --> 02:46.997
Yeah.
No.
Well, how's it going?

02:46.997 --> 02:48.249
It's good.

02:48.249 --> 02:49.960
Penny and I found a place
near Preminger.

02:49.960 --> 02:51.001
It's really nice.
Aww.

02:51.001 --> 02:51.842
An apartment?
Yeah.

02:51.842 --> 02:52.883
Is it small?

02:52.883 --> 02:54.465
It has two bedrooms,

02:54.465 --> 02:58.178
and it's really close
to some really great schools.

02:58.178 --> 03:00.261
You picked schools?

03:00.261 --> 03:02.303
No, I brought these
so that we could decide,

03:02.303 --> 03:04.435
so that we could talk about
the possibilities.

03:04.435 --> 03:07.187
You picked brochures.
It sounds like you're decided.

03:07.187 --> 03:09.310
Uh, she's going to school
in New York?

03:09.310 --> 03:10.481
Well, I mean, if she does,

03:10.481 --> 03:12.152
she would need to fill out
an application,

03:12.152 --> 03:14.024
which, actually,
I meant to talk to --
Um [sighs] okay.
I'm sorry.

03:14.024 --> 03:17.368
We need to take, um,
a big step backwards.

03:17.368 --> 03:19.660
Somewhere, sometime you heard me
say yes to this.

03:19.660 --> 03:21.622
You heard me say,
"Yes, please, Callie,

03:21.622 --> 03:23.494
take my daughter
across the country."

03:23.494 --> 03:25.956
But I never said that.

03:25.956 --> 03:27.538
I did not.
I said we could talk about it.

03:27.538 --> 03:29.089
No.
Callie, what you said was,

03:29.089 --> 03:32.463
"You'll be able to see Sofia
whenever you want."

03:32.463 --> 03:33.834
Okay,
that's not what I meant.

03:33.834 --> 03:36.337
I'll "be able"
to see her.

03:36.337 --> 03:38.839
I was just excited about
making this move. That's all.

03:38.839 --> 03:41.141
Go. Be happy.

03:41.141 --> 03:42.343
Have your Penny.

03:42.343 --> 03:44.555
You're ju-- You're not taking
my daughter with you.

03:44.555 --> 03:46.437
Please stop saying
your daughter.

03:46.437 --> 03:47.898
She's --
But she is my daughter,

03:47.898 --> 03:50.230
and she's yours,
and she lives here.

03:50.230 --> 03:52.613
So I don't know why we're
talking about schools over there

03:52.613 --> 03:55.316
and bedrooms and...

03:55.316 --> 03:57.358
I --
Why can't she come visit you?

03:57.358 --> 03:58.489
'Cause that's not...

03:58.489 --> 04:00.991
Okay.
that's why we're here.

04:00.991 --> 04:02.953
That -- That's what
we're talking about.

04:02.953 --> 04:05.326
That -- We are just discussing
what the options are.

04:05.326 --> 04:08.749
That's not
what it sounds like.

04:08.749 --> 04:11.502
[ Siren wails in distance ]

04:11.502 --> 04:14.254
How's Hot Rock Star?

04:14.254 --> 04:17.177
Filthy as ever.
And creative.

04:17.177 --> 04:18.429
I know, right?

04:18.429 --> 04:20.431
I've got to keep coming up
with new names for his...

04:20.431 --> 04:22.553
-[ Chuckles ]
-Oh, no.

04:22.553 --> 04:24.184
What's wrong?

04:24.184 --> 04:25.306
Kyle is in town,

04:25.306 --> 04:27.348
and he wants to take me
out to dinner.

04:27.348 --> 04:28.849
I don't understand
your face.

04:28.849 --> 04:31.352
Mm, no.
No, I'm not going.

04:31.352 --> 04:33.814
Uh, why not?
Free food with bonus hot guy?

04:33.814 --> 04:36.817
Uh, well, we're doing very well
right now with our fingers,

04:36.817 --> 04:37.988
so why screw with it?

04:37.988 --> 04:39.320
[ Chuckling ] You mean
by actually screwing.

04:39.320 --> 04:41.782
[ Cellphone chimes ]
[ Chuckles ]
This is fun,

04:41.782 --> 04:44.615
but we don't actually have
anything in common.

04:44.615 --> 04:46.827
You know, do surgeons
even date musicians?

04:46.827 --> 04:48.909
[ Cellphone chimes ]
-[ Groans ]
-He is very chatty.

04:48.909 --> 04:52.002
No, this is Grey.
She wants labs back on her...

04:53.624 --> 04:56.757
No. No.

04:56.757 --> 04:57.878
What now?

04:57.878 --> 04:59.380
No. I just sent something
very filthy...

04:59.380 --> 05:00.721
[ Chuckles ]
Well, isn't that the point?

05:00.721 --> 05:02.593
-...to Meredith Grey.
-Oh!

05:02.593 --> 05:04.345
-Undo, undo!
-Undo! Undo! Undo! Undo!

05:04.345 --> 05:07.307
No! There's no undo!
There's no undo!

05:07.307 --> 05:09.730
[ Elevator dings ]

05:11.602 --> 05:12.733
Thanks.

05:14.525 --> 05:15.986
There you are.
I know.

05:15.986 --> 05:18.318
Uh, and, Dr. Grey,
I'm so sorry.

05:18.318 --> 05:21.111
You should be.
Did you get Sheila's labs?

05:21.111 --> 05:23.444
Dr. Grey.
What?

05:23.444 --> 05:25.115
Nothing.

05:25.115 --> 05:27.908
Or thank you.
Uh, you're a very classy lady.

05:27.908 --> 05:29.580
Hey, Sheila,
good morning.

05:29.580 --> 05:31.331
-This is Dr. Edwards.
-Hi.

05:31.331 --> 05:33.333
She will be assisting me
in surgery this afternoon.

05:33.333 --> 05:36.166
Uh, Sheila Davis.
5-centimeter hepatic adenoma.

05:36.166 --> 05:39.169
Uh, scheduled for laparoscopic
resection this afternoon.

05:39.169 --> 05:41.382
-She's off O.C.P.s for --
-Could you hand me my purse?

05:41.382 --> 05:42.843
I think
I have a hairbrush in there.

05:46.016 --> 05:47.928
Sure.
Trying to look good for surgery?

05:47.928 --> 05:50.020
[ Chuckles ]
Not for surgery. For him.

05:50.020 --> 05:52.312
-James is coming today.
-Oh, that's great.

05:52.312 --> 05:54.024
-Uh, James?
-My boyfriend.

05:54.024 --> 05:55.686
-Ooh.
-Sort of.

05:55.686 --> 05:59.109
I mean, "soul mate" is gross,
but, yes, my boyfriend.

05:59.109 --> 06:01.652
I'm finally meeting him today,
and I look like this.

06:01.652 --> 06:03.784
You haven't met
your boyfriend?

06:03.784 --> 06:05.285
-Not in person.
-They met online.

06:05.285 --> 06:06.326
-A year ago.
-Oh.

06:06.326 --> 06:08.619
And it's been
the most amazing year.

06:08.619 --> 06:10.330
Only over texts.

06:10.330 --> 06:12.913
Then I told him
about my surgery,

06:12.913 --> 06:14.995
and he said he had to be here --
canceled everything.

06:14.995 --> 06:17.418
-That's really sweet.
-I know it sounds crazy.

06:17.418 --> 06:18.669
You can get a lot done
in a text.

06:18.669 --> 06:19.960
What am I doing?

06:19.960 --> 06:22.302
I mean, why would I want him
to meet me like that?

06:22.302 --> 06:23.804
He's going to be expecting
my profile pic,

06:23.804 --> 06:25.676
and I don't really even look
that good on my best day.

06:25.676 --> 06:27.428
Hey, you look fine.

06:27.428 --> 06:28.559
[ Sighs ]

06:28.559 --> 06:30.140
And Dr. Edwards
completely understands.

06:30.140 --> 06:32.853
She has a first date today, too.
A big one.

06:32.853 --> 06:33.974
Huge, apparently.

06:33.974 --> 06:35.355
Really? That's so nice.

06:35.355 --> 06:37.938
No. It's still
up in the air.

06:37.938 --> 06:39.279
Oh.

06:39.279 --> 06:42.823
Well, we will be back
to prep you for surgery. Okay?

06:42.823 --> 06:44.655
Let's go, Edwards.

06:46.447 --> 06:48.829
Apparently,
you got my text.

06:48.829 --> 06:50.991
Oh, yeah.
I got it good.

06:50.991 --> 06:52.993
Obviously
it was not meant for you.
[ Chuckles ]

06:52.993 --> 06:55.085
I hope not,
because it sounds so painful.

06:55.085 --> 06:56.376
It was very unprofessional,

06:56.376 --> 06:58.248
and I should have been
more careful.

06:58.248 --> 07:00.501
Edwards, you really should
save your energy,

07:00.501 --> 07:01.802
because
you're gonna need it.

07:01.802 --> 07:03.504
Can we skip ahead to the part
where this joke is old?

07:03.504 --> 07:05.596
No.
Did you really do this?

07:05.596 --> 07:07.508
I have...not.

07:07.508 --> 07:09.680
I've -- I've --
I was riffing on...

07:09.680 --> 07:11.101
You --

07:11.101 --> 07:13.353
Okay.

07:13.353 --> 07:14.935
I'm sorry. I'm confused.
Your son is here?

07:14.935 --> 07:15.936
-Yes!
-Yes!

07:15.936 --> 07:17.357
We think so.
Hers. Or mine.

07:17.357 --> 07:18.769
-They said there was a shooting.
-Who said -- Who said that?

07:18.769 --> 07:20.060
The police.
When they called, we were --
We were --

07:20.060 --> 07:21.061
We were at work,
and -- and our sons

07:21.061 --> 07:22.442
are at -- at home
with the sitter.

07:22.442 --> 07:24.775
The last names
are Green and Cole.
Can you just look it up?

07:24.775 --> 07:26.066
-I'm here.
-I'm sorry.

07:26.066 --> 07:28.328
I don't see any record here
for either of those names.

07:28.328 --> 07:29.990
I got paged.
Gunshot kid?

07:29.990 --> 07:31.331
They said the ambulance
was coming here.

07:31.331 --> 07:32.663
Wait, "gunshot kid."
That -- is that our kid?

07:32.663 --> 07:33.784
Karev, let's move.

07:33.784 --> 07:35.666
We have an incoming GSW.
Victim's 8 years old.

07:35.666 --> 07:36.877
Oh, my God!

07:36.877 --> 07:38.499
Our sons are both 8 years old.
Which one is it?

07:38.499 --> 07:39.840
Which one of our sons
has been shot?

07:39.840 --> 07:41.542
Ma'am, we'll know more soon.
But right now --

07:41.542 --> 07:43.173
Right now, we just need you
to have a seat,

07:43.173 --> 07:45.045
and we'll get back to you
when we know something.

07:45.045 --> 07:47.177
Oh, please,
let them both be alive.
Come with me.

07:47.177 --> 07:48.849
Come with me.
Come with me.

07:48.849 --> 07:53.393
[ Siren wailing ]
♪ Tender is the light
that shines on you ♪

07:55.355 --> 07:58.358
♪ Gentle is the morning
made anew ♪

07:58.358 --> 08:00.521
Guys, I appreciate
that you want to help,

08:00.521 --> 08:01.732
but all I need right now

08:01.732 --> 08:04.234
are Hunt, Wilson,
and maybe cardio and neuro.

08:04.234 --> 08:06.106
So, the rest of you can go.

08:07.487 --> 08:09.660
♪ My love ♪

08:09.660 --> 08:11.451
[ Siren continues ]

08:13.914 --> 08:19.169
Wonder why
you wish your life away

08:19.169 --> 08:21.712
♪ Waiting for the perfect boat ♪

08:21.712 --> 08:23.834
-Don't!
-No, we have to see who it is!

08:23.834 --> 08:25.215
Ma'am, ma'am,
please stay back.
♪ To take ♪

08:26.547 --> 08:35.596
♪ Waiting for the perfect wind
to sail away ♪

08:38.348 --> 08:41.441
Woman: 8-year-old male,
GSW to the abdomen.

08:41.441 --> 08:44.404
Stable after 500 cc bolus NS.

08:45.736 --> 08:47.608
Who is it?
I can't see him.

08:47.608 --> 08:48.859
We're -- We're gonna
take care of him.

08:48.859 --> 08:51.111
It's all right. We're gonna
take care of him, okay?

08:51.111 --> 08:55.155
♪ You hold your happiness
away from you ♪

08:55.155 --> 08:57.578
♪ Whoa-oh-oh-oh-oh,
whoa, oh, oh ♪

08:57.578 --> 08:59.329
No!

08:59.329 --> 09:04.665
No, it's Brandon!
It's Brandon!
♪ Stop where you are ♪

09:04.665 --> 09:06.166
Oh, thank God.

09:06.166 --> 09:10.130
♪ Under fading stars ♪

09:10.130 --> 09:12.973
Peter!
Peter, there you are.

09:12.973 --> 09:17.057
♪ There is no better place,
it's true ♪

09:17.057 --> 09:18.348
Get him inside.

09:18.348 --> 09:21.141
♪ Light a fire where you are ♪
Coming through.

09:21.141 --> 09:22.312
Brandon, Mommy's here!
I love you!

09:22.312 --> 09:24.735
Ma'am, we've got him.
We've got him.

09:24.735 --> 09:25.986
♪ Underneath a blanket
of the cold ♪

09:25.986 --> 09:27.527
E.T. tube
in good position.

09:27.527 --> 09:29.820
Breath sounds
clear and equal bilaterally.

09:29.820 --> 09:31.571
Well, does anyone know
what happened?

09:31.571 --> 09:32.953
Was it a drive-by?
♪ Lying in the dark,
your seeds will grow ♪

09:32.953 --> 09:33.904
Where the hell
was the babysitter?

09:33.904 --> 09:34.995
Hey, everybody, shush!

09:34.995 --> 09:37.287
Owen: A GSW to
the right upper quadrant.

09:37.287 --> 09:38.909
Belly is soft.
♪ Miracles just like
a winter rose ♪

09:38.909 --> 09:40.661
Okay. [ Clears throat ]
I'm gonna need a...

09:40.661 --> 09:41.962
-An ultrasound.
-Mm-hmm.

09:41.962 --> 09:43.253
You know -- you know,
let me get in there.

09:43.253 --> 09:44.504
I'll -- I'll --
I'll do it.
♪ Will be ♪

09:44.504 --> 09:46.336
He's a little tachycardic,
but his pulse is strong.

09:46.336 --> 09:48.298
Shepherd, any reflexes?

09:48.298 --> 09:49.509
Spinal shock. The bullet must
have penetrated the spinal cord.

09:49.509 --> 09:50.841
♪ Give up all the things
you can't control ♪

09:50.841 --> 09:52.843
All right, let's get him to CT.
Everyone clear the room.

09:52.843 --> 09:54.264
All right, you heard him.
Thank you and goodbye.

09:54.264 --> 09:55.345
♪ Still yourself
and watch them come and go ♪

09:55.345 --> 09:56.847
-Okay, ready?
-Okay.

09:56.847 --> 09:58.058
Call us if you need us.

09:58.058 --> 10:00.931
Ready and...
On my count -- 1, 2, 3.

10:00.931 --> 10:02.272
Go.
♪ Wherever you are,
you'll find... ♪

10:02.272 --> 10:03.563
Pierce.

10:03.563 --> 10:07.648
♪ ...you're home... ♪
We're good, thanks.

10:07.648 --> 10:09.900
Easy.
♪ ...at last ♪

10:23.373 --> 10:24.454
Sofia's doing really well.

10:24.454 --> 10:26.166
You know,
she loves her dance class,

10:26.166 --> 10:27.167
and why would we take her
out of school in the
middle of the year?

10:27.167 --> 10:28.508
No, no, no.
No, no, no.

10:28.508 --> 10:29.800
We wouldn't move her until after
school's over for the year.

10:29.800 --> 10:31.211
Well, yeah, no.
"We" wouldn't move her anywhere.

10:31.211 --> 10:33.633
Uh, "we" is you and Penny.
Mm.

10:33.633 --> 10:37.678
You can't do this.
You don't get to just
decide to --

10:37.678 --> 10:40.681
I haven't decided anything.
I'm trying to talk to you.

10:40.681 --> 10:43.854
I'm trying to show you that
I've thought out this choice.

10:43.854 --> 10:45.435
But it's not just
your choice.

10:45.435 --> 10:47.477
To completely disrupt
our child's life --

10:47.477 --> 10:49.149
Why is it
disrupting her life?

10:49.149 --> 10:51.571
You moved three times a year
when you were a kid.

10:51.571 --> 10:54.154
You turned out pretty good.
Why isn't it just life?

10:54.154 --> 10:55.445
[ Horn honks ]

10:55.445 --> 10:56.446
I have a consult.

10:56.446 --> 10:58.198
Do you want to look
at these?

10:58.198 --> 11:00.991
No. No, I'm good.

11:00.991 --> 11:02.492
[ Siren wailing ]

11:03.744 --> 11:06.787
He's so little.
He's so little.

11:08.128 --> 11:10.630
Hey, you still have that, uh,
prenatal appointment tomorrow?

11:10.630 --> 11:12.502
Yeah, uh, at 9:00.

11:12.502 --> 11:14.594
Will you, um...

11:14.594 --> 11:16.426
Just, uh, let me know
how it goes.

11:16.426 --> 11:18.098
Absolutely.
Uh, right after.

11:18.098 --> 11:19.559
All right.
Appreciate it.

11:19.559 --> 11:21.301
Of course.

11:21.301 --> 11:23.143
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

11:25.726 --> 11:28.358
Owen: Brandon's injuries
are severe.

11:28.358 --> 11:31.441
And we're taking him up
to surgery right now.

11:31.441 --> 11:33.233
The bullet
hit his spinal cord,

11:33.233 --> 11:34.905
so at the moment
we are evaluating --

11:34.905 --> 11:36.777
-Patty.
-Stacy, are you okay?

11:36.777 --> 11:38.238
-Were you shot at?
-I'm so sorry.

11:38.238 --> 11:39.409
I left the room
for just a few minutes.

11:39.409 --> 11:40.660
Were the boys out front?

11:40.660 --> 11:41.912
Did they find
the person who did it?

11:43.323 --> 11:44.955
[ Stammers ]

11:44.955 --> 11:48.088
No.
The boys found your gun.

11:48.088 --> 11:50.380
They were playing
with it.

11:50.380 --> 11:51.962
Your gun?

11:51.962 --> 11:54.214
You have a gun?

11:54.214 --> 11:57.007
Yes, I do.
But it's locked.

11:58.508 --> 12:00.390
No.

12:00.390 --> 12:02.012
No.

12:02.012 --> 12:05.015
We were just playing.
It went off.

12:05.015 --> 12:06.476
Did I kill him?

12:06.476 --> 12:08.939
No.
Peter, no, you didn't.

12:08.939 --> 12:10.851
Peter,
Brandon's alive, okay?

12:10.851 --> 12:13.483
And we're gonna take care of him
right now.

12:13.483 --> 12:14.945
All right?

12:14.945 --> 12:16.616
I'm gonna need
to talk to you.

12:16.616 --> 12:18.819
Let's go.

12:18.819 --> 12:21.822
[ Sighs ]

12:21.822 --> 12:23.663
We don't know that.

12:23.663 --> 12:24.825
Excuse me?

12:24.825 --> 12:26.787
We told that kid that
he didn't kill his friend.

12:26.787 --> 12:27.918
He didn't.

12:27.918 --> 12:32.172
Except we don't know that.
Not yet.

12:32.172 --> 12:34.174
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. system ]

12:37.007 --> 12:38.258
Hey.

12:40.801 --> 12:43.013
Ooh.
You all right?

12:43.013 --> 12:45.976
Yeah, I just --
I needed a second.

12:45.976 --> 12:47.808
A little kid got shot.

12:47.808 --> 12:49.850
Oh, God. [ Sighs ]

12:49.850 --> 12:53.563
Yeah. It's just awful.

12:53.563 --> 12:55.775
Okay.

12:55.775 --> 12:57.818
Time's up.
Yeah.

12:57.818 --> 12:59.659
How did everything go
with Arizona?

12:59.659 --> 13:02.532
She's [sighs] not even open
to talking.

13:02.532 --> 13:04.865
It's like
she's just saying no.

13:04.865 --> 13:06.536
I'm sorry.
That sucks.

13:06.536 --> 13:08.208
Did I jump the gun here?

13:08.208 --> 13:12.292
I'm just trying to get
all the ducks in a row
so that we can talk,

13:12.292 --> 13:14.294
but it seems like she really
just wants to fight about this.

13:14.294 --> 13:15.335
Am I wrong?

13:15.335 --> 13:17.968
Yeah, I-I can't help you.

13:17.968 --> 13:21.681
There may come a time when I get
to have a say in Sofia's life,

13:21.681 --> 13:23.924
but that's definitely
not now.

13:23.924 --> 13:25.765
I'd just make things worse.

13:25.765 --> 13:30.020
So, all I can say is
I'm sorry.

13:30.020 --> 13:32.232
That sucks.

13:41.441 --> 13:42.903
Coags and LFTs
are normal.

13:42.903 --> 13:44.744
She's ready
when the O.R.'s ready.

13:44.744 --> 13:47.657
Great.
How are you feeling?

13:47.657 --> 13:48.999
Sheila, what's wrong?

13:48.999 --> 13:50.911
[ Chuckles ]

13:50.911 --> 13:52.913
Nothing.
He just texted me.

13:52.913 --> 13:56.166
He's here in the hospital,
and he brought irises.

13:56.166 --> 13:58.508
He remembered
I loved irises.

13:58.508 --> 14:01.461
It's just --
I was just freaking out.

14:01.461 --> 14:02.842
[ Chuckles ]

14:02.842 --> 14:05.765
Okay, well,
let's try to calm down.

14:05.765 --> 14:08.678
-Sheila Davis?
-Yes. Is he here?

14:08.678 --> 14:12.182
Um...yeah.

14:12.182 --> 14:13.523
Hi.

14:13.523 --> 14:14.734
What?

14:14.734 --> 14:16.816
Who are you?

14:16.816 --> 14:18.028
I'm James.

14:18.939 --> 14:20.240
Surprise.

14:20.240 --> 14:21.441
No.

14:21.441 --> 14:24.034
I-I-I know this isn't
what you're expecting.

14:24.034 --> 14:25.825
I'm -- I'm really,
really sorry about that,

14:25.825 --> 14:26.866
but I just --

14:26.866 --> 14:28.248
Oh, my God.

14:28.248 --> 14:30.120
This isn't how I wanted to do
this at all, but when you --

14:30.120 --> 14:31.081
when you told me you were sick
and you needed surgery,

14:31.081 --> 14:32.412
I just couldn't wait.

14:32.412 --> 14:34.915
-You catfished her.
-No, I-I just didn't want to --

14:34.915 --> 14:37.127
Get out.
Get out.

14:37.127 --> 14:38.498
Sheila, it's -- it's James.

14:38.498 --> 14:40.710
Get out! Get out!
We should call security.

14:40.710 --> 14:41.631
James, let's go.

14:41.631 --> 14:42.672
James.

14:42.672 --> 14:44.004
Get out!

14:44.004 --> 14:46.556
I think
we should go outside.
Oh. Oh. I just --

14:47.677 --> 14:49.849
[ Monitor beeping ]

14:49.849 --> 14:53.563
L1 shattered and left fragments
in the spinal canal.

14:53.563 --> 14:55.355
So, his mom just had a gun
laying around.

14:55.355 --> 14:56.896
Owen: She said
she had it locked up.

14:56.896 --> 14:59.019
The mom
should be locked up.

14:59.019 --> 15:00.320
Well, she might be.

15:00.320 --> 15:02.822
It could involuntary
manslaughter if --

15:02.822 --> 15:04.364
Don't even say it.
It's not gonna happen.

15:04.364 --> 15:05.905
Do you own a gun?

15:05.905 --> 15:07.657
No.
[ Chuckles ] No.

15:07.657 --> 15:10.700
No, I, uh, fix bullet holes.
I don't make them.

15:10.700 --> 15:12.492
I just mean you're in the Army.
I imagine --

15:12.492 --> 15:14.995
Well, you need one in the Army.
You don't need one here.

15:14.995 --> 15:16.336
Amelia: Well, every day,

15:16.336 --> 15:18.208
someone's kid is in an O.R.
with a gunshot wound.

15:18.208 --> 15:19.629
Every single day.

15:19.629 --> 15:21.461
When are people gonna learn?
It just makes things worse.

15:21.461 --> 15:23.673
And people always say
they need one for protection.

15:23.673 --> 15:25.005
-They don't.
-Unless they do.

15:25.005 --> 15:26.806
I have a gun.

15:26.806 --> 15:29.099
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, right.

15:29.099 --> 15:31.141
I do.
I've had one for a long time.

15:31.141 --> 15:32.512
-You have a gun.
-Mm-hmm.

15:32.512 --> 15:33.853
Why?

15:33.853 --> 15:35.225
Just like you said --
for protection.

15:35.225 --> 15:37.227
Have you used it?

15:37.227 --> 15:38.898
No. I haven't needed to,
thank God.

15:38.898 --> 15:40.320
Thank God you haven't had it
used against you.

15:40.320 --> 15:41.321
All right. Can we stop?

15:41.321 --> 15:42.562
There's a kid down there
scared to death

15:42.562 --> 15:43.823
he might have killed
his friend.

15:43.823 --> 15:45.945
There are two lives
on this table right now,

15:45.945 --> 15:48.368
so can we just stop the chatter
and pay attention?

15:49.369 --> 15:51.371
Right angle.

15:51.371 --> 15:52.622
♪♪

16:00.630 --> 16:01.671
Woman:
Let me just tell him.

16:01.671 --> 16:04.044
Yes. Thanks for holding.
Who's calling?

16:04.044 --> 16:05.545
What happened?

16:05.545 --> 16:07.717
Right.

16:07.717 --> 16:09.219
Sorry?
Well, how did you --

16:09.219 --> 16:12.552
Where were you that
they were able to get a gun?

16:12.552 --> 16:14.684
I was --

16:14.684 --> 16:16.226
I left the room
for a minute.

16:16.226 --> 16:17.227
For a minute?

16:17.227 --> 16:18.438
It was so fast.

16:18.438 --> 16:20.810
So, but why? Why?

16:20.810 --> 16:22.022
What?

16:22.022 --> 16:24.314
Did you leave your phone charger
in the car or...

16:24.314 --> 16:26.156
were you texting
or was it the TV?

16:26.156 --> 16:28.988
No! The police
already asked me all this.

16:28.988 --> 16:30.910
Yeah, why were you gone
long enough

16:30.910 --> 16:33.493
for them to unlock a drawer
or a closet or whatever

16:33.493 --> 16:35.705
and pull out a gun
and shoot it?

16:35.705 --> 16:37.917
It was your job
to keep them safe.

16:37.917 --> 16:39.669
It was literally your job.

16:39.669 --> 16:41.211
And I was doing my job.

16:41.211 --> 16:43.583
The boys aren't babies.
They're 8.

16:43.583 --> 16:45.465
They go off
and they play together.

16:45.465 --> 16:48.968
I don't have to watch over them
every single second.

16:48.968 --> 16:51.221
They're good boys.

16:51.221 --> 16:54.184
I-I should be able
to go to the bathroom

16:54.184 --> 16:56.436
or warm them up
some mac and cheese

16:56.436 --> 16:57.897
without them
shooting each other.

16:57.897 --> 16:58.848
Dr. Pierce.

16:58.848 --> 17:02.272
[ Crying ]
I was just making them food!

17:02.272 --> 17:03.773
This wasn't my fault!

17:03.773 --> 17:07.647
Can I get you to take a look
at something, please?

17:07.647 --> 17:09.109
[ Crying ]

17:09.109 --> 17:12.202
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

17:12.202 --> 17:14.114
Did they call someone
for you?

17:14.114 --> 17:16.116
Is your mom coming?

17:16.116 --> 17:18.918
Uh, Dr. Pierce.

17:23.503 --> 17:26.336
I spent every day for
an entire year talking to him,

17:26.336 --> 17:28.758
and he's just...a liar.

17:28.758 --> 17:30.670
Of course, I'm the idiot
who let it happen.

17:30.670 --> 17:32.802
I mean, I told him that
I loved him before we even met.

17:32.802 --> 17:33.843
Who the hell does that?

17:33.843 --> 17:35.265
Well, you were ready
for something good.

17:35.265 --> 17:36.476
Yeah, plus, sometimes

17:36.476 --> 17:39.018
someone can seem really,
really good onscreen.

17:39.018 --> 17:40.600
-True.
-Sometimes too good.

17:40.600 --> 17:43.273
He was good onscreen.
I know.

17:43.273 --> 17:45.895
Oh, my God. Oh, Go--
No, no, no.

17:45.895 --> 17:48.488
What --
What is he doing here?

17:48.488 --> 17:49.489
Wait.
That's your date?

17:49.489 --> 17:51.241
That's the guy
you were gonna do the --

17:51.241 --> 17:52.572
-Please don't.
-I mean, I wouldn't.

17:52.572 --> 17:53.823
I'm classy, remember?

17:53.823 --> 17:55.155
Hi. What are you --

17:55.155 --> 17:57.197
Hey.
Uh, I'm working.

17:57.197 --> 17:58.328
I'll -- I'll --
I'll walk with you.

17:58.328 --> 17:59.579
I'm, uh, Kyle Diaz.

17:59.579 --> 18:02.162
Hi, Kyle.
I feel like I know you.

18:02.162 --> 18:03.583
What are you doing here?

18:03.583 --> 18:04.664
You said you couldn't wait
to see me.

18:04.664 --> 18:06.005
I said a lot of things.

18:06.005 --> 18:07.337
-She did.
-This is my life.

18:07.337 --> 18:08.708
I get James and you get that.

18:08.708 --> 18:10.210
You really need to leave.
I'm working.

18:10.210 --> 18:12.422
You know, Edwards, you can go
and catch up if you need to.

18:12.422 --> 18:13.803
See?
We get to catch up.

18:13.803 --> 18:15.265
No, we really --
I don't need to catch up.

18:15.265 --> 18:18.848
Uh, you really need to leave
because I need to go operate.

18:18.848 --> 18:20.180
Can I watch?

18:20.180 --> 18:21.891
See you do your thing?

18:21.891 --> 18:23.143
-No.
-No?

18:23.143 --> 18:24.564
No, it's private, okay?
[ Elevator dings ]

18:24.564 --> 18:27.527
The O.R. is a private place,
and you can't watch.

18:27.527 --> 18:30.150
I'm working!
This is an O.R. elevator.

18:30.150 --> 18:33.153
You can't go in here, either.
The O.R. is a sterile area.

18:33.153 --> 18:35.155
You are not sterile.

18:35.155 --> 18:37.577
You are...very, very dirty.

18:37.577 --> 18:40.740
♪♪

18:40.740 --> 18:42.662
Robbins.

18:42.662 --> 18:45.205
I've been working on
the resident rotation schedule.

18:45.205 --> 18:46.296
Okay.

18:46.296 --> 18:47.837
Yeah, and losing Warren
and Blake --

18:47.837 --> 18:49.799
I mean, soon enough,
it's gonna have an impact.

18:49.799 --> 18:51.251
Yeah.

18:51.251 --> 18:53.012
Um...

18:53.012 --> 18:55.635
would you care if you lost
a resident for a few days

18:55.635 --> 18:57.597
while I get things
settled?

18:57.597 --> 18:59.559
-No.
-I'll give you two interns.

18:59.559 --> 19:01.181
No! No!
Why is it just me?

19:01.181 --> 19:02.432
Why are you taking
my resident away?

19:02.432 --> 19:04.184
Why am I the one that's just
gonna roll over and take it?

19:04.184 --> 19:05.685
And why don't you go
screw someone else over?

19:05.685 --> 19:08.067
Robbins, you might want
to take it down a notch.

19:08.067 --> 19:10.610
[ Sighs ]

19:10.610 --> 19:12.402
Callie's moving to New York.

19:12.402 --> 19:14.984
What?

19:14.984 --> 19:16.616
And she's trying
to take Sofia with her.

19:16.616 --> 19:17.947
Can she do that?

19:22.662 --> 19:25.044
Hey.
What are you doing here?

19:25.044 --> 19:26.956
I'm doing it.

19:26.956 --> 19:29.249
You're doing what?

19:29.249 --> 19:31.000
Something other than
literally --

19:31.000 --> 19:33.343
literally watching
the clothes dry at my house.

19:33.343 --> 19:35.675
-Slow down.
-I'm meeting with Don Heller.

19:37.507 --> 19:38.558
Seriously?

19:38.558 --> 19:39.679
Yes. Yes.

19:39.679 --> 19:42.181
Look, I have seven years
in anesthesiology.

19:42.181 --> 19:43.182
It's perfect.

19:43.182 --> 19:45.855
I can work, help people,
earn money,

19:45.855 --> 19:47.567
and get time in the O.R.

19:47.567 --> 19:49.188
Everybody wins.

19:49.188 --> 19:51.361
All right. What does --
What does Bailey think
about this?

19:51.361 --> 19:53.813
Well, listen,
it might not even pan out.

19:53.813 --> 19:56.155
Right. I mean, why tell her
until it's a real thing?
That's what I thought.

19:56.155 --> 19:57.487
-Just keep it to ourselves.
-Until we know.

19:57.487 --> 19:59.909
[ Sighs ] You realize
that's a terrible idea, right?

19:59.909 --> 20:01.030
It's a great idea.

20:01.030 --> 20:02.782
I wish you luck, sir.

20:02.782 --> 20:04.704
♪♪

20:05.825 --> 20:07.997
It's a great idea.

20:09.539 --> 20:10.830
I don't see
any residual bleeding.

20:10.830 --> 20:12.632
-Can you get a good look?
-Yeah.

20:12.632 --> 20:15.004
[ Sighs ]

20:16.636 --> 20:18.388
Amelia: Definite CSF leak.

20:18.388 --> 20:20.510
We'll need to remove
the entire vertebral body

20:20.510 --> 20:22.802
to decompress the spinal cord,
right?
Mm-hmm.

20:22.802 --> 20:25.935
Problem is, I'll need to dissect
more of the aorta.

20:25.935 --> 20:27.807
Risking paralysis?
Is there another option?

20:27.807 --> 20:29.018
Put him in a brace.

20:29.018 --> 20:30.690
Then he wouldn't be
completely decompressed.

20:30.690 --> 20:32.111
So, we risk paralyzing him
either way.

20:32.111 --> 20:34.063
What are you gonna do?

20:34.063 --> 20:37.357
Do I have time
to talk to his mom?

20:37.357 --> 20:40.570
Both the brace and the surgery
carry some risk of paralysis.

20:40.570 --> 20:42.572
My recommendation
is the surgery.

20:42.572 --> 20:45.244
It's very delicate,
but I would like to try it.

20:45.244 --> 20:47.537
My husband's on his way.
Do I have to decide right now?

20:47.537 --> 20:49.369
I'm afraid we can't wait.

20:49.369 --> 20:52.872
Okay. Okay. Um,
then please do whatever you can.

20:52.872 --> 20:55.795
But he'll survive,
either way, right?

20:55.795 --> 20:57.337
-Danielle.
-We're working very hard.

20:57.337 --> 20:59.048
He'll pull through.
I know he will.

20:59.048 --> 21:00.680
Danielle,
will you shut up?!

21:00.680 --> 21:01.681
What?

21:01.681 --> 21:03.473
You better hope
he pulls through.

21:03.473 --> 21:05.555
This is not Peter's fault.
He is a child.

21:05.555 --> 21:07.056
But the gun
was locked away.

21:07.056 --> 21:08.728
They shouldn't have been
in my room.
This is not the time --

21:08.728 --> 21:10.560
Oh, don't you dare
get righteous with me.

21:10.560 --> 21:12.942
That was your house
and your gun

21:12.942 --> 21:15.565
and your kid that knew about it,
not mine.

21:15.565 --> 21:19.278
I sent my child
over to your house to play,

21:19.278 --> 21:22.572
and your kid might have made him
a murderer.

21:22.572 --> 21:25.535
♪♪

21:33.583 --> 21:34.794
-Hey.
-Hi.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.466
I called the sitter.
The kids are okay.

21:36.466 --> 21:37.507
What's wrong?
What happened?

21:37.507 --> 21:38.758
Nothing. Nothing.

21:38.758 --> 21:40.009
I just wanted to make sure
they're okay, and they are.

21:40.009 --> 21:41.180
What's wrong with you?

21:41.180 --> 21:43.723
Oh. Okay,
you guys haven't heard.

21:43.723 --> 21:45.515
An 8-year-old came in today,

21:45.515 --> 21:47.727
GSW, accidentally shot
by his friend.

21:47.727 --> 21:48.978
Oh.

21:48.978 --> 21:50.189
Oh, wow.

21:50.189 --> 21:52.852
Anyway, just wanted to check in,
you know?

21:52.852 --> 21:54.524
Okay.
Yeah.

21:57.026 --> 22:00.860
Man, I just...
kids with guns.

22:00.860 --> 22:01.991
Stop that.

22:01.991 --> 22:04.494
We're not doing this.
It's too sad.

22:04.494 --> 22:06.576
Shake it off.
We can be sad later.

22:06.576 --> 22:09.078
We're talking juvie GSW
during my surgery.

22:11.751 --> 22:14.003
Richard, she offered me
visitation rights

22:14.003 --> 22:15.294
to see my own daughter.

22:15.294 --> 22:17.166
Well, I-I'm sure she didn't mean
it that way, Arizona.

22:17.166 --> 22:18.257
How else would she mean it?

22:18.257 --> 22:19.719
My lawyer says
it's an indication that --

22:19.719 --> 22:21.220
Your lawyer?

22:21.220 --> 22:22.922
Yes, I have to
protect myself.

22:22.922 --> 22:25.054
I know
you feel like you do.

22:25.054 --> 22:26.386
But you and Torres

22:26.386 --> 22:29.639
have always figured out
this stuff beautifully.

22:29.639 --> 22:30.850
Just slow down.

22:30.850 --> 22:32.642
I just watched
Jackson and April --

22:32.642 --> 22:34.143
Yeah, I know. So did I.
It was a mess.

22:34.143 --> 22:35.274
A mess started

22:35.274 --> 22:36.686
with overreactions
and misunderstandings.

22:36.686 --> 22:38.478
So, what?
Now I'm overreacting?

22:38.478 --> 22:42.111
I'm saying Sofia's too important
not to ask yourself if you are

22:42.111 --> 22:46.035
before you do something
that can't be undone.

22:46.035 --> 22:49.118
You're right.
Of course.

22:49.118 --> 22:51.911
You're right. I know.

22:54.123 --> 22:55.665
Retract more cephalad.

22:55.665 --> 22:57.336
Great.

22:57.336 --> 22:58.798
So, what's your deal?

22:58.798 --> 23:01.260
I'll establish vascular control,
and --

23:01.260 --> 23:03.843
No, I meant about your date,
the one you blew off out there.

23:03.843 --> 23:07.557
There is no deal.
What's your deal?

23:07.557 --> 23:09.098
Excuse me.
You're not supposed
to tell me

23:09.098 --> 23:10.349
to take my time
to go see a guy.

23:10.349 --> 23:12.101
You're supposed to tell me
to hurry up and prep.

23:12.101 --> 23:15.314
Can you please do your job
and make my life miserable?

23:15.314 --> 23:17.016
I'm just saying,
after all those texts,

23:17.016 --> 23:18.648
and then that's the way
you treat him?

23:18.648 --> 23:20.149
'Cause the texts
are all it is.

23:20.149 --> 23:22.732
Yeah, it's been a few weeks,
and it's good and hot, but...

23:22.732 --> 23:24.654
[ Chuckles ] I know.
It's on my phone.

23:24.654 --> 23:26.446
The expectations
are too high.

23:26.446 --> 23:27.987
There can only be disappointment
from here.

23:27.987 --> 23:29.158
You don't know that.

23:29.158 --> 23:31.911
I know I am a very good
"on paper" person.

23:31.911 --> 23:34.333
I mean, I shine.
I'm amazing.

23:34.333 --> 23:39.839
But when it comes to being
an "in person" person, I...

23:39.839 --> 23:41.841
You said you wanted to work
and not talk,

23:41.841 --> 23:43.633
so can we focus on the work,
please?

23:43.633 --> 23:45.715
I said I didn't want to talk
about sad stuff.

23:45.715 --> 23:47.426
I'm okay to talk about
this stuff.

23:47.426 --> 23:48.678
Graspers.

23:48.678 --> 23:50.309
Although,
this is its own kind of sad.

23:50.309 --> 23:52.682
Hell.
I'm in actual Hell right now.

23:52.682 --> 23:54.013
Well, you said
to make you miserable.

23:54.013 --> 23:56.976
♪♪

23:56.976 --> 24:00.359
Dr. Shepherd,
BP is going down.

24:00.359 --> 24:01.981
How's that
bone graft coming?

24:01.981 --> 24:05.024
Owen: It's out.
Sealing up with bone wax.

24:05.024 --> 24:06.275
[ Clears throat ]

24:07.697 --> 24:09.489
It's in the house?

24:09.489 --> 24:11.240
What?

24:11.240 --> 24:14.163
The gun.
Where is it in the house?

24:14.163 --> 24:16.996
It's in a safe place.

24:16.996 --> 24:18.998
I didn't even know it was there.
I want to know where it is.

24:18.998 --> 24:20.500
It's in a box
under the bed.

24:20.500 --> 24:21.581
It's under our bed?!

24:21.581 --> 24:23.002
That's where we'd need it.

24:23.002 --> 24:24.253
I don't want a gun
in my house.

24:24.253 --> 24:26.385
It's my house, too.
It makes me feel safer.

24:26.385 --> 24:28.257
-Does it?
-Have you seen our neighborhood?

24:28.257 --> 24:30.089
Because you're not safer.
You're more likely to get hurt

24:30.089 --> 24:31.591
because of a freakin' gun
around.
Alex.

24:31.591 --> 24:32.802
I got shot once.
You know that.

24:32.802 --> 24:34.433
[ Monitor beeping ]

24:34.433 --> 24:35.645
[ Clears throat ]

24:35.645 --> 24:38.187
Owen: BP's 60 over 40.
Starting him on levo.

24:38.187 --> 24:39.358
Once I decompress
the spinal cord,

24:39.358 --> 24:40.439
it should get better.

24:40.439 --> 24:42.522
I just --
Just let me work.
Work faster.

24:44.734 --> 24:47.486
♪♪

24:56.245 --> 24:57.537
You okay?

24:57.537 --> 24:59.879
Yeah. Just watching.

24:59.879 --> 25:03.082
He's hypotensive now.

25:03.082 --> 25:04.463
You'd make a good cop.

25:06.005 --> 25:07.757
You nearly broke
that babysitter.

25:07.757 --> 25:09.839
[ Sighs ]
I don't know what I was doing.

25:09.839 --> 25:11.340
Why did I do that?

25:11.340 --> 25:13.512
I watch my sister's kids
all the time.

25:13.512 --> 25:15.975
And last week,
I turned away for one second,

25:15.975 --> 25:18.267
and my nephew had dumped
an entire bag of flour

25:18.267 --> 25:19.348
on the kitchen floor.

25:19.348 --> 25:21.270
He's 3.

25:21.270 --> 25:22.351
And I thought,

25:22.351 --> 25:24.734
"What if that had been
a pot of boiling water?"

25:24.734 --> 25:27.987
I'm not used to this --

25:27.987 --> 25:32.652
being scared like this,
worrying like this.

25:32.652 --> 25:36.155
They're not even my kids.

25:36.155 --> 25:38.207
Oh, I get it.

25:38.207 --> 25:41.661
They're family.

25:41.661 --> 25:43.583
Family messes you up.

25:45.625 --> 25:47.216
That part's new for me.

25:50.930 --> 25:52.301
[ Knock on door ]

25:52.301 --> 25:53.552
Got a minute?

25:53.552 --> 25:55.054
Ben. What are you --

25:55.054 --> 25:56.976
I just came by to, uh --

25:56.976 --> 25:59.058
[ Chuckles ] You know,
I-I had a nice conversation

25:59.058 --> 26:00.850
with Don Heller just now.
You did?

26:00.850 --> 26:03.522
Yeah. I thought I could
pick up some cases as
an anesthesiologist,

26:03.522 --> 26:05.024
and he said he'd be happy
to have me --

26:05.024 --> 26:07.316
No, absolutely not.
I said, "Great.
When can I start?"

26:07.316 --> 26:08.648
Ben, no.

26:08.648 --> 26:10.740
I can't sit around that house
for five more months, Miranda.

26:10.740 --> 26:11.741
You're suspended.

26:11.741 --> 26:13.613
Sitting around
is the damn point.

26:13.613 --> 26:16.826
I am suspended from
the surgical residency program.

26:16.826 --> 26:18.117
I won't be operating.

26:18.117 --> 26:20.159
And I can stay current
in the O.R.

26:20.159 --> 26:21.500
I can earn a living.

26:21.500 --> 26:23.002
Nobody's gonna go hungry.

26:23.002 --> 26:25.625
Look, what's it gonna look like
if the staff sees you

26:25.625 --> 26:27.707
sitting in surgery
like nothing happened?

26:27.707 --> 26:28.968
It's gonna look like
I'm working.

26:28.968 --> 26:31.510
It'll make me look
like I'm --
You? You?

26:31.510 --> 26:32.842
See, it's always
about your job,

26:32.842 --> 26:34.513
what's gonna make you
look good or bad.

26:34.513 --> 26:35.845
Well,
what am I supposed to do?

26:35.845 --> 26:37.516
I don't know,
but you're not doing this.

26:37.516 --> 26:41.350
You run Surgery,
not Anesthesia.

26:41.350 --> 26:43.022
You're not chief there.

26:43.022 --> 26:45.394
It's not your department.
It's not your call.

26:45.394 --> 26:48.357
Ben.
You can do this.

26:48.357 --> 26:50.609
Oh, I know I can.
But if you do,

26:50.609 --> 26:51.781
you better figure out
where you're gonna sleep.

26:55.945 --> 26:58.197
[ Door slams ]

26:58.197 --> 26:59.659
How you doing?

26:59.659 --> 27:02.411
Micro Penfield 4.
Just a few more --
[ Alarm beeping ]

27:02.411 --> 27:04.503
He's in V-tach,
rate of 233.

27:04.503 --> 27:06.085
-Paddles!
-No, no paddles.

27:06.085 --> 27:08.087
His spine is completely unstable
and exposed right now.

27:08.087 --> 27:09.508
We have to.
If you shock him,

27:09.508 --> 27:10.880
he will move
and he will be paralyzed.

27:10.880 --> 27:12.251
You'll undo all my work.

27:12.251 --> 27:14.133
We'll try
and take him down with meds.

27:14.133 --> 27:15.715
Push Amiodarone,
125 milligrams.

27:15.715 --> 27:18.017
Just give me a minute.
Add vaso on top
of his pressors.

27:18.017 --> 27:19.679
-V-fib.
-Shepherd, we have to shock him.

27:19.679 --> 27:21.681
-Charge to 50.
-No! If he moves, he won't walk.

27:21.681 --> 27:23.973
If he dies,
he won't walk, either. Clear.

27:23.973 --> 27:25.314
[ Paddles whine ]
Amelia, clear!

27:25.314 --> 27:27.476
Just give me -- Damn it!

27:27.476 --> 27:28.567
Clear.

27:28.567 --> 27:29.979
[ Thump ]

27:31.771 --> 27:34.033
[ Breathing deeply ]

27:42.832 --> 27:44.083
Is Sheila okay?

27:44.083 --> 27:46.585
James, Sheila was very clear.
She wants you to leave.

27:46.585 --> 27:48.087
I love her.
I wasn't trying to lie.

27:48.087 --> 27:49.248
Should I call security?

27:49.248 --> 27:50.589
We talked online every day.

27:50.589 --> 27:52.341
We understand each other
in a way that --

27:52.341 --> 27:54.754
I've never been seen like that
or loved like that --

27:54.754 --> 27:55.795
for who I am.

27:55.795 --> 27:57.717
Well,
not exactly who you are.

27:57.717 --> 27:59.849
Yes. Who I am,
not just what I look like.

27:59.849 --> 28:01.851
So, when she asked to see
my picture,

28:01.851 --> 28:04.013
I-I looked at myself
in the mirror and...

28:04.013 --> 28:05.514
I got scared.

28:05.514 --> 28:07.436
I knew this could happen.
I'm not stupid.

28:07.436 --> 28:10.860
But then, when she was dying,
I had to risk it.

28:10.860 --> 28:12.111
Well, she wasn't dying.

28:12.111 --> 28:13.482
Her tumor, I mean.

28:13.482 --> 28:14.814
It was a benign tumor.

28:14.814 --> 28:16.736
The chances of it killing her
were very, very low.

28:16.736 --> 28:18.317
Excuse me?

28:18.317 --> 28:20.029
Yeah.

28:21.821 --> 28:23.322
You told me
you were dying!

28:23.322 --> 28:24.914
Get out.
You said you had
a malignant tumor.

28:24.914 --> 28:26.746
You said you were 6'2".

28:26.746 --> 28:28.497
How could you lie
straight to my face?
It wasn't even your face,
you liar.

28:28.497 --> 28:29.999
-You said you were dying!
-You said you had hair!

28:29.999 --> 28:31.460
Yeah, I can't believe
I'd fall for someone as
superficial as you!

28:31.460 --> 28:32.501
A person does not get
to call me superficial...

28:32.501 --> 28:34.333
Uh, are you calling security
or am I?

28:34.333 --> 28:35.504
I will,

28:35.504 --> 28:37.006
and I will handle
Sheila's post-op.

28:37.006 --> 28:38.177
You're done here.

28:38.177 --> 28:39.508
Pardon me?

28:39.508 --> 28:42.011
Edwards, go.
Bite the bullet.
Go on the date.

28:42.011 --> 28:44.183
It's better than being lonely
and crazy like me

28:44.183 --> 28:45.845
or having sex with your phone
in the residents' lounge.

28:45.845 --> 28:47.226
Can you not --

28:47.226 --> 28:49.148
Go.
And don't text me from it.

28:49.148 --> 28:50.519
James: You owe me $500!

28:50.519 --> 28:52.311
Sheila: You owe me
a year of my life back!

28:52.311 --> 28:53.813
God,
I told you I loved you.

28:53.813 --> 28:54.814
Stop yelling at me.
So, you do love me.

28:54.814 --> 28:56.776
No, no.
I loved a stranger!

28:56.776 --> 28:58.277
Security.

28:58.277 --> 29:00.029
[ Radio chatter ]

29:00.029 --> 29:03.532
Oh.

29:03.532 --> 29:05.244
Oh.

29:05.244 --> 29:06.745
What is it, Torres?

29:06.745 --> 29:09.128
No, uh -- We had a meeting
scheduled for now,

29:09.128 --> 29:10.249
but you're busy.

29:10.249 --> 29:13.082
-What's it about?
-Um, it can wait.

29:13.082 --> 29:14.874
Not gonna get any less busy,
Torres.

29:14.874 --> 29:16.085
Just tell me.
I'd rather --

29:16.085 --> 29:17.336
[ Chuckles ]
I'd rather wait.

29:17.336 --> 29:18.677
What is it?

29:18.677 --> 29:21.590
I'm moving to New York
with Penny Blake.

29:21.590 --> 29:23.262
I'm leaving Grey-Sloan.

29:23.262 --> 29:26.595
Uh, excuse us, please.
Mm-hmm. Sure.

29:26.595 --> 29:27.847
When?

29:27.847 --> 29:31.060
Well, Penny starts work
in a couple of months,

29:31.060 --> 29:34.443
so first I need to get
some things squared away.

29:34.443 --> 29:35.484
Like a job?

29:35.484 --> 29:36.986
Uh, I already have an offer
from NYU,

29:36.986 --> 29:38.657
and Columbia's
been calling,

29:38.657 --> 29:40.659
so there's been
a couple of other --

29:40.659 --> 29:42.401
They offered you
Chief of Ortho?

29:42.401 --> 29:44.323
No.
Um, it'll be fewer hours.

29:44.323 --> 29:46.405
And Penny's working a lot,
so...

29:46.405 --> 29:48.667
And I'm hoping
to have Sofia there.

29:50.169 --> 29:51.831
What?

29:51.831 --> 29:53.672
I mean, your career --

29:53.672 --> 29:56.335
You're a chief.
She's a resident.

29:56.335 --> 29:57.967
So, you're giving up
your career

29:57.967 --> 29:59.678
to chase tail
across the country?

30:01.680 --> 30:03.512
I just wanted
to give you notice.

30:03.512 --> 30:05.184
And I don't need
your judgment.

30:05.184 --> 30:06.515
Arizona's already
got that covered.

30:09.268 --> 30:11.140
[ Sighs ]

30:15.604 --> 30:16.815
Hey.
Start her on D5 half.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.437
I'll be back
in about a half an hour.
Uh-huh. Okay.

30:18.437 --> 30:21.070
[ Cellphone rings ]

30:21.070 --> 30:23.402
Hi. This is Dr. Robbins.

30:23.402 --> 30:25.995
I'm sorry. From where?

30:25.995 --> 30:29.658
♪ Sometimes I wonder ♪
Yes, I am.

30:29.658 --> 30:31.160
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, you bet I have a minute.

30:31.160 --> 30:32.751
♪ How it would be ♪

30:32.751 --> 30:35.334
There's a chance
of some recovery of movement,

30:35.334 --> 30:37.166
but it's very small.

30:37.166 --> 30:39.378
He'll get physical
and occupational therapy

30:39.378 --> 30:41.340
to help him regain
some function,

30:41.340 --> 30:42.551
find some new ways --

30:42.551 --> 30:44.673
But he'll
never walk again?

30:44.673 --> 30:47.096
I'm sorry.
It's very unlikely.

30:47.096 --> 30:51.020
♪ Until the work got too hard,
now it's long gone ♪

30:51.020 --> 30:53.522
The gun was locked up.

30:53.522 --> 30:56.525
It was supposed to be locked
in a drawer. It was.

30:56.525 --> 30:58.737
-I don't know how they --
-Kids watch.

30:58.737 --> 31:00.980
♪ You cut just deep enough ♪

31:00.980 --> 31:03.112
They pick up
everything you do.

31:03.112 --> 31:05.114
♪ In my dreams ♪

31:05.114 --> 31:08.787
I'm very sorry
that this happened.
♪ You keep showing up ♪

31:10.079 --> 31:16.956
♪ You were a nice placekeeper ♪

31:16.956 --> 31:18.958
[ Indistinct conversation ]

31:18.958 --> 31:24.213
♪ I couldn't see it
at the time ♪

31:25.764 --> 31:32.311
♪ You gave my love
a place to rest, to hide ♪

31:32.311 --> 31:33.892
Hey.

31:33.892 --> 31:35.394
Brandon didn't die?

31:35.394 --> 31:37.516
No. He didn't.

31:37.516 --> 31:40.899
[ Crying ]
But he can't walk?

31:40.899 --> 31:43.482
And he can't ride bikes?

31:43.482 --> 31:45.945
♪ You cut just deep enough ♪

31:45.945 --> 31:48.867
[ Sniffles ]
Is he mad at me?

31:48.867 --> 31:55.244
♪ In my dreams
you keep showing up ♪

31:56.956 --> 31:59.628
If it had been Brandon
who hurt you,

31:59.628 --> 32:01.340
would you be mad at him?

32:01.340 --> 32:04.253
♪ Don't bother to say hello ♪

32:04.253 --> 32:07.386
A little.
But it was just an accident.

32:07.386 --> 32:08.968
Right.

32:08.968 --> 32:11.310
So, I want you
to promise me something.

32:11.310 --> 32:13.642
Whenever you feel bad
about this,

32:13.642 --> 32:14.893
I want you to say,

32:14.893 --> 32:18.017
"It was an accident.

32:18.017 --> 32:19.858
I didn't mean to."

32:19.858 --> 32:22.861
I know that.

32:22.861 --> 32:24.943
But you have to know it,
too.

32:24.943 --> 32:27.366
So, you got to promise me
you will say,

32:27.366 --> 32:30.990
"I didn't mean to."

32:33.162 --> 32:35.664
We can go now, right?
We're free to go?

32:35.664 --> 32:36.955
Will you promise me that?

32:36.955 --> 32:38.747
Peter, honey,
it's time to go.

32:38.747 --> 32:41.000
♪ You were a nice placekeeper ♪

32:41.000 --> 32:44.423
♪ You were a nice ♪
Thank you.

32:44.423 --> 32:47.716
♪ Placekeeper ♪

32:47.716 --> 32:49.888
♪♪

32:59.648 --> 33:01.940
♪♪

33:03.312 --> 33:05.364
[ Keys jingling ]

33:05.364 --> 33:09.238
Well, Brandon's doing fine.
His BP's...

33:14.663 --> 33:18.667
I lived in my car
when I was 16 years old.

33:18.667 --> 33:22.501
Every night,
trying to fall asleep,

33:22.501 --> 33:24.213
I would listen
to the voices --

33:24.213 --> 33:25.674
people going by,

33:25.674 --> 33:30.509
people who had
nothing going on,

33:30.509 --> 33:33.802
nothing going for them,
nothing to lose,

33:33.802 --> 33:36.515
scared to death that they would
break in and take my stuff,

33:36.515 --> 33:38.267
take me.

33:38.267 --> 33:43.982
This gun made me feel like
I had something,

33:43.982 --> 33:46.235
something on them.

33:46.235 --> 33:48.147
But then, today...

33:50.319 --> 33:54.783
That little boy
will never walk again.

33:54.783 --> 33:56.285
Jo, he's still alive.

33:56.285 --> 33:57.496
Barely.

34:00.159 --> 34:03.122
You know, back then,
I...

34:03.122 --> 34:06.044
I didn't value my life
all that much,

34:06.044 --> 34:09.878
but [sighs]

34:09.878 --> 34:11.170
it's different now.

34:11.170 --> 34:15.674
I've outgrown this.

34:15.674 --> 34:18.477
I don't need it anymore.

34:18.477 --> 34:20.349
I don't want it.

34:26.395 --> 34:29.148
[ Sighs ]

34:36.655 --> 34:38.117
[ Sighs ]

34:38.117 --> 34:41.660
♪♪

34:41.660 --> 34:44.123
I thought
we were getting drinks.

34:44.123 --> 34:46.545
Your exact words were
"somewhere special."

34:46.545 --> 34:49.298
[ Chuckles ]
Come on.

34:49.298 --> 34:52.841
This is, uh --
This is the holy ground.

34:52.841 --> 34:56.845
Also the dirty ground
with the dirty rugs and --

34:56.845 --> 35:00.139
[Chuckles] Have they ever
cleaned any of these?

35:00.139 --> 35:01.930
No, they'll never change
anything in here --

35:01.930 --> 35:03.272
the paint or the rugs.

35:03.272 --> 35:04.813
They don't -- They don't really
want to mess with the --

35:04.813 --> 35:08.437
with the acoustics, you know,
or the, uh -- or the mojo.

35:08.437 --> 35:11.860
Every major musician
from Seattle has recorded here.

35:11.860 --> 35:13.152
Hmm?

35:13.152 --> 35:15.073
And now me.

35:15.073 --> 35:19.328
All I wanted
was just to record here,

35:19.328 --> 35:23.202
right here, this --
this very room.

35:23.202 --> 35:25.083
Huh.
You know, this is --

35:25.083 --> 35:27.836
This is where I-I feel
the most like myself.

35:27.836 --> 35:31.670
This is the me
that I like the most.

35:31.670 --> 35:33.962
Yeah, I get that.
I get that.

35:33.962 --> 35:36.635
The O.R.'s kind of
that way for me.

35:36.635 --> 35:39.057
You know,
the feel of the scrub brush,

35:39.057 --> 35:42.181
the smell of the antiseptic --
It's just --

35:42.181 --> 35:46.024
The air changes
when you walk in.

35:46.024 --> 35:47.686
It gets cold.

35:47.686 --> 35:50.819
You can feel your mind sharpen
as you step up to the table.

35:50.819 --> 35:52.321
Yeah, it's like --
like you turn it up a notch.

35:52.321 --> 35:53.532
Or a bunch of notches.

35:53.532 --> 35:54.983
Like you get charged.

35:54.983 --> 35:56.735
Yeah, right.

35:56.735 --> 35:59.488
[ Chuckles ]

35:59.488 --> 36:02.120
Okay.

36:02.120 --> 36:03.452
I like it.

36:03.452 --> 36:05.123
Okay. Whew!
[ Laughs ]

36:05.123 --> 36:07.376
Thank you.
Thank you.

36:07.376 --> 36:08.917
[ Sighs ]

36:08.917 --> 36:10.048
Come on.

36:10.048 --> 36:11.250
What is this?
What is this? "Come on?"

36:11.250 --> 36:12.671
Aren't you gonna play
something for me?

36:12.671 --> 36:14.253
Oh, you want me
to play for you?

36:14.253 --> 36:15.254
Isn't that your move?

36:15.254 --> 36:16.845
Don't you play
for all the girls?

36:16.845 --> 36:18.677
Hey, it's my life.

36:18.677 --> 36:20.799
You know,
when I'm playing,

36:20.799 --> 36:23.352
it's how I let someone in,
let someone see, uh --

36:23.352 --> 36:24.683
[ Both laugh ]

36:24.683 --> 36:25.934
-Okay, it's my move, right?
-Yeah. [ Laughs ]

36:25.934 --> 36:27.226
It's my move.

36:27.226 --> 36:28.937
But, uh, it always works,
though.

36:28.937 --> 36:30.188
Yeah, I bet.
[ Chuckles ]

36:35.404 --> 36:37.155
You want me
to play for you?

36:45.494 --> 36:48.877
Kyle,
you don't need moves.

36:48.877 --> 36:51.880
[ Parson James'
"Stole the Show" plays ]

36:57.676 --> 37:00.929
♪ Darlin', darlin' ♪

37:00.929 --> 37:03.682
♪ Oh, turn the lights
back on now ♪

37:03.682 --> 37:05.183
♪ Watching, watching ♪

37:05.183 --> 37:06.345
Okay. I'm ready.
Let's go.

37:06.345 --> 37:07.436
I just want to
go see the kids.

37:07.436 --> 37:09.017
♪ As the credits
all roll down ♪

37:09.017 --> 37:11.310
I did something very good
today.
♪ Crying, crying ♪

37:11.310 --> 37:12.651
I pushed two hearts together.

37:12.651 --> 37:13.982
♪ You know we're playing
to a full house ♪

37:13.982 --> 37:16.064
I forwarded
the cause of love.

37:16.064 --> 37:19.698
[ Crying ]
What's wrong?
What's wrong?

37:19.698 --> 37:20.989
♪ No heroes, villains,
one to blame ♪

37:20.989 --> 37:23.492
I-I don't know
how you do it, Mer.
Do what?

37:23.492 --> 37:25.414
♪ While wilted roses
filled the stage ♪
Love your kids like this.

37:25.414 --> 37:27.536
♪ And the thrill,
the thrill is gone ♪
I really love them.

37:27.536 --> 37:29.868
-They love you, too.
-No, I love them like --

37:29.868 --> 37:33.081
If something happened to them,
I would die.

37:33.081 --> 37:37.005
Like, my heart is so wide open,
and they're so fragile.

37:37.005 --> 37:38.377
♪ Our debut
was a masterpiece ♪
I don't know how you live
like this.

37:38.377 --> 37:39.718
I don't.

37:39.718 --> 37:42.140
♪ But in the end,
for you and me ♪
It's awful.

37:42.140 --> 37:45.304
♪ Oh, the show, it can't go on ♪

37:45.304 --> 37:47.976
Sometimes, you just
have to push through it,

37:47.976 --> 37:51.560
push the awful aside,
just get through the day.

37:51.560 --> 37:55.063
♪ We used to have it all,
but now's our curtain call ♪

37:55.063 --> 37:56.655
♪ So hold for the applause ♪
Hey.

37:56.655 --> 37:58.156
Hey.

37:58.156 --> 37:59.448
♪ Oh-oh-oh oh-oh-oh-oh-oh ♪

37:59.448 --> 38:01.239
I think
you saved that boy today.

38:01.239 --> 38:02.531
♪ And wave out to the crowd ♪

38:02.531 --> 38:03.702
I paralyzed that boy today.

38:03.702 --> 38:05.364
♪ And take our final bow ♪

38:05.364 --> 38:06.665
I was too slow.

38:06.665 --> 38:09.167
♪ Oh, it's our time to go ♪
No, I meant Peter.

38:09.167 --> 38:12.331
♪ But at least
we stole the show ♪

38:12.331 --> 38:13.832
♪ At least
we stole the show ♪

38:13.832 --> 38:15.003
Nathan...

38:15.003 --> 38:17.295
♪ At least
we stole the show ♪

38:17.295 --> 38:18.877
Nathan cheated on
my sister.

38:18.877 --> 38:20.629
I know.

38:20.629 --> 38:23.011
I, uh -- I...

38:23.011 --> 38:27.346
And when she found out,
she called.

38:27.346 --> 38:29.518
She told me.

38:29.518 --> 38:31.640
And I said --

38:31.640 --> 38:35.354
[ Sighs ] I said...

38:35.354 --> 38:38.146
"Just forget about him.

38:38.146 --> 38:39.738
Walk away.

38:39.738 --> 38:42.030
Just get on a chopper
and come to me."

38:42.030 --> 38:44.993
I told my sister
to get on that helicopter.

38:44.993 --> 38:47.536
♪ We're cryin', cryin' ♪

38:47.536 --> 38:48.657
I did it.

38:48.657 --> 38:52.040
♪ So let the velvet
roll down ♪

38:52.040 --> 38:53.161
And...

38:53.161 --> 38:54.583
♪ Down ♪

38:54.583 --> 38:57.626
...that was the last thing
I ever said to her.

38:57.626 --> 38:58.877
♪ ...One to blame ♪

38:58.877 --> 39:01.299
♪ While wilted roses
fill the stage ♪

39:01.299 --> 39:02.801
♪ And the thrill ♪

39:02.801 --> 39:06.885
♪ The thrill is gone ♪

39:06.885 --> 39:09.848
♪ Our debut
was a masterpiece ♪

39:09.848 --> 39:12.561
♪ Our lines we read
so perfectly ♪

39:12.561 --> 39:13.812
♪ But the show... ♪

39:13.812 --> 39:14.853
You didn't mean to.

39:14.853 --> 39:16.645
♪ ...it can't go on ♪

39:19.317 --> 39:22.360
♪ We used to have it all ♪

39:22.360 --> 39:25.614
♪ But now's our curtain call ♪
Hey.

39:25.614 --> 39:27.325
Got a late one, huh?

39:27.325 --> 39:29.578
I do.
Everything okay?

39:29.578 --> 39:33.622
I wondered if you wanted to go
in the morning to the OB.

39:33.622 --> 39:35.333
O-Of course I do. Yeah.

39:35.333 --> 39:36.585
Good. [ Chuckles ]

39:36.585 --> 39:38.917
Baby should know
that you're there.

39:38.917 --> 39:40.999
I will be there.

39:40.999 --> 39:42.090
Uh, 9:00 a.m.?

39:42.090 --> 39:43.381
Sure.

39:49.057 --> 39:50.218
[ Monitor beeping ]

39:50.218 --> 39:53.972
Hey, there he is.
Glad to see you, man.

39:53.972 --> 39:55.013
Glad it all worked out.

39:55.013 --> 39:57.726
Yep.
Yep, it worked out.

39:57.726 --> 40:01.359
Once we fire that first shot,
we're committed.

40:01.359 --> 40:04.152
♪ But the band plays on now ♪

40:04.152 --> 40:06.655
♪ We're cryin', cryin' ♪

40:06.655 --> 40:11.029
♪ So, let the velvet
roll down ♪

40:11.029 --> 40:14.332
God, she was so little.

40:14.332 --> 40:16.374
You remember
when Sofia was in here

40:16.374 --> 40:21.089
and you could see her heartbeat
in her whole body?

40:21.089 --> 40:25.173
God, how impossibly tiny
she was.

40:25.173 --> 40:27.596
I can't believe our girl
was ever that little.

40:27.596 --> 40:29.347
There's almost no way
to take it back.

40:29.347 --> 40:31.550
♪ Our lines we read
so perfectly ♪

40:31.550 --> 40:32.931
♪ But the show ♪

40:32.931 --> 40:35.854
I jumped the gun.
I'm so sorry.

40:35.854 --> 40:39.818
I was carried away
when I first told you.

40:39.818 --> 40:42.110
[ Chuckling ] And I've done
everything wrong since.

40:42.110 --> 40:43.652
[ Sighs ]

40:43.652 --> 40:45.614
Sofia is our little girl,

40:45.614 --> 40:49.277
and I am not trying
to make plans without you.

40:49.277 --> 40:50.829
Please believe that.

40:50.829 --> 40:52.871
The Barton School
called me.

40:52.871 --> 40:55.994
They wanted to talk to me
about her application,

40:55.994 --> 40:57.335
which they loved.

40:57.335 --> 40:58.497
They called you?

40:58.497 --> 40:59.838
So, tell me
that part again

40:59.838 --> 41:01.459
about how you're not
making plans?

41:01.459 --> 41:03.341
You know how these things work.
There are waiting lists.

41:03.341 --> 41:05.003
It doesn't mean that
I actually tried to make --

41:05.003 --> 41:06.505
We're not talking
about this anymore.

41:06.505 --> 41:08.547
Hey, you don't get
to decide that. I'm going.

41:08.547 --> 41:10.138
I don't want to
leave Sofia behind,

41:10.138 --> 41:11.680
so we have to
work out something.

41:11.680 --> 41:13.892
Yeah, I just mean that
you're not talking to me
about it anymore.

41:13.892 --> 41:15.854
The question becomes --

41:15.854 --> 41:17.766
Do we keep firing back...

41:17.766 --> 41:18.937
You got a lawyer?

41:18.937 --> 41:20.809
Yeah.
You can talk to her.

41:20.809 --> 41:23.652
♪ At least
we stole the show ♪

41:23.652 --> 41:25.864
You hired a lawyer.

41:25.864 --> 41:27.485
Yes.

41:27.485 --> 41:29.658
Now who's jumping the gun?

41:29.658 --> 41:34.072
You started this.

41:34.072 --> 41:37.956
♪ And wave out to the crowd ♪

41:37.956 --> 41:40.328
♪ And take our final bow ♪

41:40.328 --> 41:41.960
All right.

41:41.960 --> 41:43.882
...and declare
an all-out war?

41:43.882 --> 41:45.964
♪ But at least
we stole the show ♪
